{{Infobox company | name = Boris Banović | logo = Banovic logo.png | former_name = | type = Private | foundation = | founder = Boris Banović | location_city = | location_country = [[Croatia]] | location = [[Zagreb]] | locations = | area_served = | key_people = Boris Banović, president & founder | industry = Fashion | products = Clothing and Accessories | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | caption = | homepage = {{url|www.borisbanovic.com}} | footnotes = | intl = }}
'''Boris Banović''' is a [[Croatia]]n fashion designer and luxury clothing brand operating out of [[Zagreb Airport|Zagreb]], Croatia. The brand specializes in high end, tailor made clothing for men and women in an urban business style.
==Designer== Boris Banović (10 May 1973, Zagreb) is a Croatian fashion designer and TV personnel, also known by the name Fashion Guru. He is also a TV host, critic, columnist, fashion editor, book writer, announcer, guest on various fashion shows, TV presenter and member of the Showtime jury (Croatian version of American Idol).Banović was born in [[Zagreb, Croatia]], where he finished Faculty of Textile Technology and got his college degree. Ambitious and determined to succeed as a designer, Banović went to [[London]] for further education in interior design.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://novatv.dnevnik.hr/clanak/redcarpetekipa/fashion-guru.html|title=Fashion Guru|author=|work=NovaTV.hr|accessdate=17 November 2014}}</ref> He began his career as a fashion buyer, fashion editor, columnist, TV person and book writer and was known as Fashion guru. His book, “Vodič za urbane frajere”, is a guide book aimed at urban men, who are not burdened with the idea that they must be supermen, about rules of social conduct and it is first of its kind in Croatia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.profil-mozaik.hr/vodic-za-urbane-frajere/PR/138936|title=Vodič za urbane frajere|publisher=Adria Media Zagreb D.O.O|accessdate=17 November 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129023056/http://www.profil-mozaik.hr/vodic-za-urbane-frajere/PR/138936|archivedate=29 November 2014|df=}}</ref> Now, after years of hard work, Banović is a successful fashion designer and opened his own fashion shop.
==Clothing lines== His desire has always been to have his own fashion brand. After he started his own TV show and proved himself as a fashion buyer, he launched his company and his first autumn collection in spring 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dnevnik.hr/showbuzz/celebrity/boris-banovic-kao-dizajner-ipak-sam-malo-vise-nego-drugi-na-udaru-kritika---307474.html|title=Boris Banović Business|author=|work=dnevnik.hr|accessdate=18 November 2014}}</ref>
===Boris Banović=== It is a brand for urban business men and women who want to look serious and classic, yet modern. His 5 collections are in line with classic, tailor made design. His fashion is a combination of sporty and classic. The purchase is possible in stores (Zagreb, Dubrovnik and Rijeka) and through other distribution channels, such as online shops or some concept shops.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gloria.hr/pogledajte-i-kritzirajte-prva-dizajnerska-kolekcija-fashion-gurua/|title=Boris Banović's First Designer Collection|author=|work=gloria.hr|accessdate=18 November 2014}}</ref> [[File:Boris Banović collection.jpg|thumb|Boris Banović collection]]
===Boris Banović 2014=== In 2014, Banović designed high fashion clothes for both men and women. The 2014 collection is inspired by retro Russian gangster style with black, blue and white as predominant colors.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.index.hr/rouge/clanak/boris-banovic-predstavio-lookbook-za-svoju-nosivu-kolekciju-za-proljeceljeto-2014/751127.aspx|title=Collection Spring/Summer 2014.|author=|work=index.hr|accessdate=18 November 2014}}</ref>
===2B Design=== This is an everyday casual, sporty, more relaxed line of clothing for both men and women.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fashion.hr/2b-boris-banovic.aspx|title=2B Design|publisher=fashion.hr|accessdate=18 November 2014}}</ref> His summer 2014 is his Signature Line for Ultra Europe, the world-famous music festival. It is a wild, trendy, colorful look for young EDM fans and enthusiasts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fashion.hr/boris-banovic-dizajni|title=Ultra Europe Collection|author=|work=fashion.hr|accessdate=18 November 2014}}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> [[File:2B Design.jpg|thumb|2B Design]]
==Fashion Guru== Fashion Guru is Banović's alias under which he wrote numerous columns, fashion critics and reviews. He started working for tportal in 2004, and by 2005, he got his own column, Stars. From 2006, as a part of TV show, ''Red Carpet'', he hosted a 20-minute TV report about fashion and fashion shows, stars, new trends and lifestyle.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://novatv.dnevnik.hr/clanak/redcarpetekipa/fashion-guru.html|title=Fashion Guru|author=|work=NovaTV.hr|accessdate=17 November 2014}}</ref>
